    &lt;Title&gt;1st class&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Rebecca Hodgson&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I am writing this review regarding my recent experience with the Maxillofacial department at BRI where I was under the care of the consultant and his wonderful team. 

I am aware that some people are only too quick to criticise and complain when they believe they have been subject to poor or inadequate treatment. Sadly those same people are often slow to recognise superb treatment when it is delivered.

My experience from start to finish was 1st class. I was listened to and treated with the utmost respect and professionalism at all times.  Any issues or questions I had were resolved quickly with great compassion and care. 

The consultant and his colleagues were kind and reassuring. Nothing was too much trouble for them. 

I underwent surgery at the Maxillofacial unit at The Bradford Royal Infirmary on 21 May 2019. Having concerns about my recovery I contacted the hospital  and was seen very quickly. This resulted in a further consultation on Tuesday 28th May when my concerns were allayed as a result.

I was so grateful to him and everyone in his team not only for their patience and expertise, but also for treating me as a person with dignity and kindness.

I was very worried as I waited for the results of the biopsies taken from my mouth and I know that the consultant was aware of my concerns. Today, 30 May 2019 I received a telephone call from him the context of which was that the analysis suggested a low grade infection rather than anything more sinister.

As you can imagine my relief was indescribable. This kind action just goes to evidence the humanity and thoughtfulness I have witnessed during my treatment

The consultant I saw and his team are a credit to the medical practice in general and the NHS in particular. 

Rebecca Hodgson&lt;/CommentText&gt;
